    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1868-04-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1868-04-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="190"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d190">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Thornton</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1868-04-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 17, 1868.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Referring to your communication of the 23d
                    ultimo, relative to the ill treatment of two British subjects by the public
                    authorities in North Peru, and to the proceedings of the United States consul at
                    Lambayeque in regard thereto, I have the honor to inclose for your information a
                    translation of a note<note n="*" xml:id="d190fn1">For this inclosure see
                        correspondence with the Peruvian legation.</note> of the 1st instant, upon
                    the subject, which Mr. Garcia, the Peruvian minister, has addressed to this
                    department.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, with the highest consideration, sir, your obedient
                    servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edward Thornton,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                            &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
